research_municipality_step.notes: Humble, TX operates under a Council-Manager form of government. The city council consists of a Mayor and five Council Members elected from the city at large for specific 'Places'. There was conflicting information regarding the Council Member for Place 1, with one source indicating 'Vacant' and a more recent meeting agenda listing Andy Curry. Similarly, for Place 5, one source listed Rick Swanson while a more recent agenda listed David Pierce, who also serves as Mayor Pro Tem. The information from the May 2024 meeting agenda was prioritized for current officials.
